g.title: CPU state after reset - CS:IP = F000:FFF0 - CR0.PE = 0 - 20-bit addressing - No memory protection
GDTR points to valid GDT - Null descriptor at offset 0 - Kernel CS at offset 0x08 - Kernel DS at offset 0x10
Protection Enable bit set - mov cr0, eax with PE=1 - CPU now in protected mode - Segments still have old values!
Far jump flushes prefetch - jmp 0x08:protected_entry - Clears 16-bit instruction queue - Reloads CS with selector 0x08
All segment registers valid - DS, ES, FS, GS = 0x10 - SS = 0x10 - All using protected mode selectors
Full protected mode operation - 32-bit addressing - Memory protection active - Privilege levels enforced - Ready for paging setup
